@page "/doc"
@model PetBox.Web.Pages.Doc.IndexModel
@{
	ViewData["Title"] = "PetBox docs";
	Layout = "_PublicLayout";
}
	<main class="max-w-3xl mx-auto p-6">
		<h1 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4" data-testid="doc-index-title">PetBox documentation</h1>
		<p class="text-sm opacity-70 mb-6">
			Public, no sign-in required — safe to open from an agent or share by link.
		</p>
		<ul class="flex flex-col gap-3" data-testid="doc-index-list">
			<li class="card bg-base-200 border border-base-300">
				<a href="@Routes.DocOverview()" class="card-body p-4 hover:text-primary" data-testid="doc-link-overview">
					<div class="font-semibold">PetBox overview</div>
					<div class="text-sm opacity-70">
						What PetBox is, the modules (config, logs, data, dashboard, tasks/memory/sessions) and how
						to consume them — REST/MCP and the published client libraries. Start here.
					</div>
				</a>
			</li>
			<li class="card bg-base-200 border border-base-300">
				<a href="@Routes.DocOnboarding()" class="card-body p-4 hover:text-primary" data-testid="doc-link-onboarding">
					<div class="font-semibold">Agent onboarding (staged runbook)</div>
					<div class="text-sm opacity-70">
						The end-to-end sequence — mint on Connect → one <code>petbox-wire</code> command →
						comprehension → first real plan — with a validation gate at every stage. Start here
						when bringing an agent online.
					</div>
				</a>
			</li>
			<li class="card bg-base-200 border border-base-300">
				<a href="@Routes.DocWire()" class="card-body p-4 hover:text-primary" data-testid="doc-link-wire">
					<div class="font-semibold">Wire a project (petbox-wire CLI)</div>
					<div class="text-sm opacity-70">
						The operator guide to the CLI: wiring a project, the commands (update / apply / doctor /
						roles / profile), generated agent files, the offline cache and the exit codes.
					</div>
				</a>
			</li>
			<li class="card bg-base-200 border border-base-300">
				<a href="@Routes.DocAgent()" class="card-body p-4 hover:text-primary" data-testid="doc-link-agent">
					<div class="font-semibold">MCP surface reference</div>
					<div class="text-sm opacity-70">
						What PetBox exposes over MCP, the board/node model, the full tool list, and the SKILL.md
						contents <code>petbox-wire</code> installs. Also the manual registration steps for
						harnesses it doesn't cover yet (<code>omp</code>, <code>pi</code>).
					</div>
				</a>
			</li>
			<li class="card bg-base-200 border border-base-300">
				<a href="@Routes.DocMethodology()" class="card-body p-4 hover:text-primary" data-testid="doc-link-methodology">
					<div class="font-semibold">Methodology cheatsheet (agent)</div>
					<div class="text-sm opacity-70">
						The operational contract for the spec / work / idea rails: board kinds, node fields,
						links, effects, the approve gate, and what goes where.
					</div>
				</a>
			</li>
			<li class="card bg-base-200 border border-base-300">
				<a href="@Routes.DocPhilosophy()" class="card-body p-4 hover:text-primary" data-testid="doc-link-philosophy">
					<div class="font-semibold">Methodology — the model (philosophy)</div>
					<div class="text-sm opacity-70">
						Why the rails are shaped this way: the two processes, the entities, the lifecycle,
						and computed surveyability.
					</div>
				</a>
			</li>
		</ul>
	</main>
